  h3 What are cookies?

  p Cookies are small data files that are placed on your computer or mobile device when you visit a website. Cookies are widely used by website owners to operate their websites, or to work more efficiently, as well as to provide information about reports.

  p Cookies defined by the website owner (in this case, #{companyName}) are called "proprietary cookies" (or "first-party cookies" or even "permanent cookies"). Cookies defined by parties other than the owner of the website are referred to as "third-party cookies". Third-party cookies allow third-party features or functionality to be provided on or through the website (for example, such as advertising, interactive content, and analytics). Parties who establish these third-party cookies may recognize your computer at a time when visiting the website in question and when visiting certain other websites.

  
  h3 Why do we use cookies?

